Commentary Text: Hardik Pandya to Arshdeep Singh, 3 runs, comedy of errors to finish the innings! Short ball, pulled hard to deep mid-wicket and they decide to risk the second run as it's the final delivery. The throw is wayward at the keeper's end and they then go for the third run that's surely not on. Should have been an easy run out but Hardik dislodged the stumps with his back foot before he could put the ball onto the stumps. The third ump has a long look at it just to be sure that both bails were off before Hardik disturbed the stumps and that was indeed the case

Commentary Text: Ferguson to Rahul Chahar, out Rabada Run Out!! 1 run completed. This is an atrocious phase of cricket from Punjab! As if the two set batters showing poor game awareness wasn't enough, their last useful batter in Rabada has run himself out. Never a second run there at all. Chahar had dabbed this towards third man and it was always just a single. But for some reason Rabada goes down for the second and by the time he turns back, he is too late. Flat throw from Shami and Wade does the rest. Even the dive isn't enough for Rabada. Rabada run out (Shami/Wade) 1(1)

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Shahrukh Khan, out Lbw!! Massive double strike from Rashid! This is why you pay the big bucks to strike bowlers, to strike big blows exactly when the team badly needs them. Got Livingstone earlier in the over and now has sent back Punjab's last big threat with the bat, Shahrukh. Another poor shot though, looking to play a wild slog sweep against a stump-to-stump delivery that straightened just a tad, and struck Shahrukh on the back leg. Looked quite good in real time and Rashid went on a long celebrappeal that eventually convinced the umpire. Shahrukh had to review it, but once there was a flat line on UltraEdge, he knew the Three Reds would come on ball tracking. Gujarat storming their way back in this contest. Shahrukh Khan lbw b Rashid Khan 15(8) [6s-2]

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Livingstone, out Caught by Miller!! This is poor game awareness from Livingstone! Taking on the opposition's only threat in his final over, that too against the longer boundary. Never a good idea and he pays the price. This wasn't short enough to pull anyway and Rashid got it to skid off the pitch, robbing Livingstone off all the timing on the shot. Hit it flat and straight down deep mid-wicket's throat. Just like the earlier games, Punjab are in danger of having an underwhelming last few overs. Excellent innings from Livingstone but he'll know deep down that he should have batted through. Livingstone c Miller b Rashid Khan 64(27) [4s-7 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Darshan Nalkande to Odean Smith, out Caught by Shubman Gill!! Two in two for Nalkande! Things do change quickly in T20, don't they? Got tonked in the last two overs but has come back with a bang in this third. Another slower one, just short of a fuller length and Smith wants to get going straightaway. Almost like Jitesh previous ball, he too miscues the loft towards long-on. An easier take this time around for Gill. These wickets could halt the charge a bit. Commentary Text: Darshan Nalkande to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Shubman Gill!! Respite for young Nalkande! Brave bowling this, slower ball and full, tempting the big shot and Jitesh looks to go over long-on. Not the best connection and Gill takes a good catch tumbling forward. Timely breakthrough for the Titans although they'd definitely have loved to get Livingstone. A wicket nevertheless. Handy cameo from Jitesh, ensured that the momentum kept going. Commentary Text: Odean Smith to Rahul Tewatia, SIX, SHE IS WON! Tewatia wins her. Two balls, two sixes, and forget these two in-the-slot, smash-me-please balls, it's what Odean Smith did on 19.4 that's the biggest culprit. Had he not overthrown, Tewatia wouldn't have been on strike, and only Tewatia could have done a Tewatia. So damn calmly, he's just walked across his stumps, crouched, and hacked this over cow corner. Punjab just cannot stop being reminded of Sharjah ..

Commentary Text: Rabada to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Mayank!! 96. And it ends. After 58 balls of just plain elegance, it's the 59th that Gill's lost his shape on, and perished. Another wide low full toss this, which he tries slicing over extra cover, only for the ball to tail away a slight bit, dip in on him, take the toe-end, and pop up to extra cover. In all the knocks that have ever been played and in all the knocks that ever will be in T20 cricket, there cannot be one with runs as beautiful as these. Shubman Gill c Mayank b Rabada 96(59) [4s-11 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Mayank!! It was the googly, and it was a little too full to be in the slot as well. But Sudharsan has premediated a slog-sweep, and thus, ends up slicing it straight up off the outside-half. Mayank, at the edge of extra cover, circles under it, nearly misjudges it as well, but then does well to stretch to his left and gobble it up. Sai Sudharsan c Mayank b Rahul Chahar 35(30) [4s-4 6s-1]
